Perl (5.18, at least) does let you (ab)use named groups to provide match-part identification.<p>Given `(?<g1>Sat)urday|(?<g2>Sun)day`, and a successful match, either `$+{g1}` or `$+{g2}` will hold the relevant subpart.<p>Quickie demo script:<p><pre><code>    my $re = &quot;(?<g1>Sat)urday|(?<g2>Sun)day&quot;;
    foreach my $d (qw(Friday Sunday Thursday Saturday)) {
        my $out = &#x27;<default>&#x27;;
        if ($d =~ /$re/) {
            if ($+{g1}) { $out = &#x27;Saturday&#x27; }
            elsif ($+{g2}) { $out = &#x27;Sunday&#x27; }
        }
        print &quot;$d routes to $out\n&quot;;
    }</code></pre>
